        "content": "<p>I am new to lean. I am searching for Galois theory in Mathlib.</p>\n<p>I have read the file Mathlib.FieldTheory.Galois. I have found the proof of The Galois correspondence from intermediate fields to subgroups, but I could not find the correspondence between Normal Subgroups and Galois intermediate fields . Does it already exist in Mathlib somewhere?</p>",
        "id": 384669902,
        "sender_full_name": "Yelong Hua",
        "timestamp": 1691996236
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"253861\">@Thomas Browning</span></p>",
        "id": 384671631,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1691996741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, but it's very close. It's a consequence of the characterizations of normality at the end of this PR: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6163\">#6163</a></p>",
        "id": 384674157,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1691997456
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what about this proposition : let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L/K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span> is a Galois extension, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> H </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> is a normal subgroup of  <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Gal}(L/K)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> E </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> is the fixed field of  <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> H </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span>, then <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\mathrm{Gal}(E/K) \\cong \\mathrm{Gal}(L/K) /H </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 384679103,
        "sender_full_name": "Yelong Hua",
        "timestamp": 1691998782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That too is not done yet, although it should follow quickly from stuff already in mathlib:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E/K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span> is normal (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=FixedPoints.normal#doc\">docs#FixedPoints.normal</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsGalois.of_fixed_field#doc\">docs#IsGalois.of_fixed_field</a>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>π</mi><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111em\"/><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333em\"/><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\pi\\colon\\mathrm{Gal}(L/K)\\to\\mathrm{Gal}(E/K)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is surjective (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AlgEquiv.restrictNormalHom_surjective#doc\">docs#AlgEquiv.restrictNormalHom_surjective</a>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">G</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>ker</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>π</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Gal}(L/K)\\cong\\mathrm{Gal}(L/K)/\\ker\\pi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Gal</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">ker</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span></span></span></span> (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=QuotientGroup.quotientKerEquivOfSurjective#doc\">docs#QuotientGroup.quotientKerEquivOfSurjective</a>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ker</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>π</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\ker\\pi=H</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">ker</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IntermediateField.fixingSubgroup_fixedField#doc\">docs#IntermediateField.fixingSubgroup_fixedField</a>)</li>\n</ul>",
