    {
        "content": "<p>Actually sorry, the first bullet point is exactly the correspondence that is not in mathlib yet (the lemmas I linked actually say that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L/E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> is normal).</p>",
